author: Fiona Flynn
title: TV | The Great Irish Bake Off
text: It's UK counterpart may have already crowned their winner, but it's time to test our baking credentials over here and see what we're made of, as The Great Irish Bake Off kicks off a new series tonight. There's a new judge on board too, as food writer Lily Higgins joins Paul Kelly, while Anna Nolan will be back on presenting duty. In tonight's opening episode, the 12 contestants tackle desserts, with each trying to create a dish inspired by a memorable moment. They also face their first technical challenge, as Paul sets them to work on exotic cheesecakes. Yum.
